#### HOW TO
# 1. Check current settings
# Open .gitconfig file: `git config --global --edit`
# Check commit message template file location on [commit] > template

# 2.Update template
# Open the commit message template file: `open file_location`

# 3. Update the file (.gitmessage)


#### COMMIT MESSAGE
# Title: [feat/fix/chore]: Summary, imperative, start upper case, don't end with a period
# No more than 70 chars.

# Add blank line between title and body.

# Body: Explain what and why (not how).

# Add blank line between body and footer.

# Footer: Include task ID (Jira issue).
